The paper is about automatic program repair, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The paper specifically focuses on condition synthesis, which involves analyzing and modifying program conditions, making programming languages (cs.PL) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also proposes using document analysis and mining frequently used predicates, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the precision of the approach, which is a security concern and falls under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
